title: For Sale/Trade:  Bluegrass Armory Viper XL 50. BMG
postcontent:
For sale is a Bluegrass Armory Viper XL 50. BMG. Rifle is an all-black right hand single shotbolt action model with 29” barrel and weighs 25 Lbs. without optics. Rifle comes in original foam cutout shippingcontainer from factory. Rifle has an excellent muzzle brake and bipod from factory that does extremely well at reducing felt recoil (but stay away from muzzle blast!!). Have only broken in and then sighted in at 100 yards (shot a cloverleaf). I attempted to shoot at 400 yards (farthest target on the range that particular day) and my scope had broken the internal adjustments and was stuck on 100 yard zero (I know I know, cheap scope). So, I have only shot it 100yards at targets and rocks so I can’t tell you how it shoots at 1,000 yards,etc… but it shoots fantastic at 100yards. Rifle has been shot exactly 41 times (have exact round cound of spent brass). Rifle comes with 46 loaded rounds of .50 BMG ball ammo (CBC brand) and 10 rounds of HSM Hornady 750 grain Amax pills (2900 fps+ with a 750 grain pill ) and 41 once fired brass.

Rifle is a great design if you are unfamiliar with the ViperXL .50. I was told they made internal parts for the Barrett M99 (single shot version that look very similar to this) but don’t know how accurate that is. But, the features, functions, and looks are very similar. 

Full disclosure, the only thing I don’t like about the ViperXL .50 is the bolt handle length (same on all models). It is really short and takes a lot ofleverage to close those big lugs and has very tight tolerances with non-match ammo. It has shot every ball ammo I’ve tried just fine, but closing the bolt with the very short bolt handle takes getting used to when you are used to a large oversized bolt. I have verified this is correct with Bluegrass through email and they confirmed they are built on tight tolerances and this is normal and not an issue or error, but I wanted to disclose so no surprises.  I was going to get a longer bolt made similar to the Barrett M99 (several inches longer) and had it quoted around $50 dollars from several places, but never went through with it since I didn’t have optics for it yet. Just to be clear, it is functionally fine, and in original factory settings and the factory confirmed this, but I like a longer bolt handle for easier leverage. 

Price is $2,600.00 OBO to your door.  $2500.00 local seattle area.

Please let me know if you have any questions.

Will only ship to FFL in states where .50 BMG is legal.

Owners manual included.

This item remains for sale until ALL arrangements are finalized with a buyer I deem, in my sole discretion, to be qualified. I reserve the right to consider multiple offers, and no offer will create a binding contract until I am satisfied with buyer qualifications, mode and terms of payment, and until all details of shipping (including insurance, packaging requirements, shipping costs, and risk of loss) are worked out. This item may be offered for sale on other internet sites.
